cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper discusses public-private networks in online social networks and their analysis. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also likely as the paper deals with social networks and their modeling. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper uses real-world DBLP records to generate public-private networks. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses algorithms for graph computing problems such as PageRank and reachability tree. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes an advanced model of attributed public-private graphs and discusses open problems in this area.
